## 12. Technical cleanup

### Delete DOCUMENTATION.md

The repo contains a 29KB DOCUMENTATION.md file. Delete it before starting the rebuild. It represents accumulated design decisions that predate this brief. This brief is the source of truth.

### Delete unused components

After the rewrite, remove:
- `LearnWithMe.tsx` (replaced by new WorkWithMe component)
- Any portfolio icons / data for deleted ventures (Gutted, OnAlert, Mindmaker Live)

### SSG / rendering

krishraja.com is a single-page SPA. With only one page, full SSR migration is overkill. However:

**Implement static pre-rendering at build time** using either:
- `vite-plugin-ssr` / Vike (overkill for one page)
- **Recommended: `react-snap`** — crawls the built SPA at build time and writes static HTML. Minimal setup, right tool for one-page sites.

This ensures all the new content renders in the HTML response for crawlers, LLMs, and link previews. Same reason Mindmaker v5 needs SSG — just at a smaller scale.

Verification: after build, `curl https://www.krishraja.com` should return the Hero H1, the operator-advisor subheadline, and the rewritten meta description in the raw HTML response.

### Performance budgets

- Homepage LCP: < 2.0s on 4G (lower than Mindmaker because there's less on the page)
- Total bundle: < 200KB gzipped
- All images: `loading="lazy"` except trust logos in Hero (keep `loading="eager"` as currently)
- Lighthouse Performance: >= 95 (personal site, one page, no excuse for < 95)

### Analytics

Keep whatever is currently installed (likely nothing visible from the meta — check). If nothing, add Plausible:

```html
<script defer data-domain="krishraja.com" src="https://plausible.io/js/script.js"></script>
